# Figma-First Implementation Gate

- Do not implement any new UI component without a design reference from Figma Desktop MCP.
- If no Figma design context is provided yet, stop and ask for it first.
- Use Figma Desktop MCP as the source of truth for structure, spacing, hierarchy, and states.
- If a user asks to implement before sharing Figma context, do not scaffold or guess the component.

# Required Workflow For Components

1. Get Figma context first (URL/node/screenshot via Figma Desktop MCP).
2. Confirm variants and states from design.
3. Implement the component to match design.
4. Iterate only after design-backed review.

# Scope

- Applies to all UI components (Accordion and every next component).
- No "temporary" component implementation without design.
